   ARKANSAS TECH NEWS




ALUMNI LEADING ACROSS THE NATION

   Excellence doesn't stop when you leave ATU. Our alumni are just getting
   started.
    1.
    2.

   rachel mouser

   RACHEL MOUSER

   Rachel works to set emergency management policies as a Senior Policy
   Analyst for the The Cadmus Group in Washington, D.C. Thanks to her
   Arkansas Tech education, Rachel was prepared to step into a national
   emergency management role.
   adena white

   ADENA WHITE

   Adena works to share the message of her local community as the Director
   of Communications at a Chamber of Commerce. Through her journalism
   degree from ATU, Adena was ready to help the organization effectively
   communicate to its members.
   kevin hern

   KEVIN HERN

   Kevin leads others as the owner of 10 McDonald’s across Tulsa, Oklahoma
   and a former CFO of McDonald’s franchises. AT ATU, Kevin learned grit,
   determination and that people matter, skills that have helped him
   succeed.
   card image 3

   ANDREA MARTIN

   Andrea is passionate about her students. As a superintendent, she sets
   the vision and path for the entire school district. Her multiple ATU
   education degrees have shaped her leadership philosophy that impacts
   the lives of hundreds of students.
   zach harris

   ZACH HARRIS

   Zach serves others as a gastroenterology fellow at a hospital in North
   Carolina. At ATU, Zach had the flexibility to create his own path
   toward his goal of being a doctor. Here, he studied emergency
   management to understand how doctors serve their community.
   card image 3

    LUKE BRADSHAW

   Luke owns Bravis Marketing Agency where he and his team create 3D
   marketing displays for businesses. With his graphic design degree from
   ATU, Luke was on the path to owning a multi-million dollar marketing
   agency.



